<br>
If it's about &quot;southern pride&quot;, then how about deciding just what it is you're proud about and what makes it southern. Maybe it's because I'm a yankee, but I don't know what's different between the South and the North enough that the American Flag - still in use and pretty definite about what it symbolizes - doesn't say it already.<br>
<br>
If it's just pride in geography, fine, but that's about as hollow as wearing pro sports team colors. There's nothing wrong with it, but there's nothing really significant about it either.<br>
<br>
If it's about racism, then there's no point in my trying to speak intelligently about it because anything intelligent is already over a bigot's head. If you're still thinking &quot;the south will rise again&quot; and get you your slaves back, then I have no problem with you waving a flag around. It will notify me from a distance that you aren't worth my time or consideration. <p>-Geln,<br>
Fool<br>
