<br>
The people in the south that I have had the &quot;pleasure&quot; of meeting are vastly different than the people where I come from. I am sure you would be able to point out various differences if you were to live in the area I am from for a year. If you were to call it for what it is, I am sure you would drudge up descriptions of white trash. Fact is, that is the truth. We have lots of that where I come from. You aren't going to offend me by describing it as that. That is your opinion and your perception. You are entitled to that...as I am entitled to mine.<br>
<br>
My viewpoints are not a blanket statement that describes every single person that lives in the south. They are, however, humorous generalizationa of quite of few of the people I have met here in the last year. Oh yes, the mullet is very much still in style hre. Hell, even some of the strippers wear mullets here in Pensacola. It is so cliche that it is funny. Well, maybe not to you...<br>
<br>
The amusing thing about jokes is that there is usually some truth in them. That's what makes them funny. That, and irony. Mullets...houses with wheels (or hosues with flat tires)...those are topics in jokes in any part of the country. Hell, everyone on my mom's side lives in a trailer. Half of my roots are about as white-trash as you can get. That doesn't mean I am going to get pissy when someone cracks a white trash joke. That would be being hypersensistive...and nobody likes hypersenstive people. <br>
<br>
Hypersensitive people humorless killjoys. Man, that would suck to be in that catagory. I'll stick with the cynical prick catagory, thanks. Hey, like I said, I call it like I see it. I know I am a cynical prick. I don't hide who I am from the world. This is me...take it or leave it. I am sure you will enjoy the latter.<br>
<br>
So, feel offended if you must. You sure as hell aren't going to change my opinion or perception about the people I have met over the last year down here...or how much different people in the south are from where I come from. And as for me...I will continue to poke fun of things that are different than my own experiences, just like most everyone else in the world does. Humor comes in many forms. I tend to participate in all of them...even the black and cynical stuff. Bummer for you if you can't appreciate any of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#77839D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karissmagentleheart>Karissma Gentleheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><TABLE STYLE=filter:Glow(color=#FF3366,strength=3><TR><TD><center><font color=#000000> <b> Huggable Motor Mouth </center></TABLE></font> </b><br> <font color=FF3366>Brick Thrower</font></span><br>  Posts: 2924<br> <font color=#F7E5C3>(11/19/02 2:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mapetite.homestead.com/files/needhugs.gif height=66 width=67></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confederate Flag:  Pride or Prejudice?</span><hr size=1> *boggles* hold up...Thank you for making me reread Froggys post. I live in the south as well. And ummm while yes there are rednecks...we arent all that way. So get a clue plz k thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#77839D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frogggystyle>Frogggystyle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Needs to Bug <br> Sy for a Title!</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#F7E5C3>(11/19/02 2:58:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeople